The paper deals with the problem of detecting signals in noise, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses applications in machine learning (cs.LG) and sensor networks (cs.SI), which are related to the problem of detecting signals in noise. Additionally, the paper presents a new analytical result, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
